RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPANISH BEAUTY took command soon after the start, continued unchallenged up front running on the turn, opened up on her rivals at the top of the stretch, was kept to the task while on the the wrong lead throughout the lane to hold safe at the finish. SILVER BULLET LADY was content sitting off the top two outside five sixteenths from the prize, angled out to the four path at the top of the lane and closed well outside to win the secondary battle nearing the finish line. UNABLE tracked behind the winner at the half, kept in close range to the frontrunner through the turn, shifted out to the three path to offer a bid but could not find another gear and stalled late losing the place award. GOLD FORESTER settled near the back on the rail in the early going, offered a mild move outside at the midpoint on the turn and found some late energy to get up for a minor share outside winning the nod at the wire. NATASHA'S BIZNIZ stalked in mid pack inside in the beginning, was nudged along on the rail three eighths from home, could not gain on the leaders and levelled out in deep stretch. GOLDEN TRAIN was off slow to trail the field down the backstretch, was hustled inside saving ground three furlongs from the finish to be in touch with the field at the quarter pole and had no response through the stretch drive. LADY IN RED settled near the rear down the backside, could not make up any ground on her rivals on the turn and was not a factor turning for home.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PETTINARI took command from the start, set the pace uncontested running on the turn, opened up of the field in upper stretch and was getting a little leg weary late but held safe when they reached the finish line. MIA AND ME was off a touch slow at the start, settled in midfield down the backstretch, was in with a chance three wide as they turned for home, angled in to the rail at the furlong marker and closed belatedly inside to get up for the place prize. TREBUCHET tracked the top two early on, rallied outside five sixteenths from the finish, had dead aim on the winner running three wide turning for home and could only finish evenly in the late stages of the race. CHUNKY MONKEY stalked between foes in the two path situated near the back to start, began to gain some with runners on either side to be in the mix for a share when they turned for home and finished with interest to get up for a minor share in the end. I'M NO SLEEPY JOE was unhurried early on trailing the pack down the backside, could see the field running on the turn and split foes in deep stretch passing tired horses. AUTUMN'S SO FLASHY broke well with the field but was slow to find his feet and was shuffled to near the back outside at the half, put in a brief run around foes three furlongs left to go, angled widest at the top of the stretch to be six wide and could not threaten. NGABE travelled in mid pack racing three deep in the early going, shifted to the rail at the half mile marker, made little impact on the fence throughout the turn and had nothing to offer for the stretch drive. OPEECHEE chased the loose leader on the rail in the beginning stages, started to weaken inside midway on the turn and retreated on the fence the last eighth.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 3 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 82. Maiden Special Weight Purse 111600. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOLO ALBUM took control from the onset, led the field into the first turn, continued to set a soft pace running down the backside, opened up on the field as they entered the top of the stretch and had more in reserve to win comfortably in the end. INDY CHAMPAGNE was allowed to settle at the rear on the inside into the first turn, advanced smartly on the fence in the backstretch entering the final turn, shifted outside five sixteenths from home commencing his rally, chased the winner in the three path throughout the stretch but could not gain and had to settle for second best. JANIS JOPLIN travelled four wide watching the winner into the first turn, continued to track outside at the half, was ridden to go after the loose leader at the quarter pole and could only finish up evenly settling on a clear third when they hit the line. ELLA FRANCES was nestled on the rail behind the frontrunning winner in the beginning, stayed in the same position down the backstretch, was scrubbed on the keep up with rivals at the two furlong pole and could make little impression throughout the stretch. INSCRUTABLE broke out at the start, stalked four wide into the first turn, trailed the field down the backside, saved ground on the rail in the final turn but could not be a presence running inside to the finish line. MILAGRE DO SOL settled in mid pack outside of rivals at the half mile marker, was coaxed for more run three furlongs to go, could not match strides with foes and gave way at the top of the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOADED QUESTION was unhurried on the rail in the beginning to be near the back of the pack, began to rally with a smart rail move with three eighths remaining, shifted out at the quarter marker for clear run, was five wide at the top of the lane and closed well wearing down her rival at the shadow of the wire. SUGAR IS GOLDEN set the fractions in the early stages, determinedly dug in on the rail up front entering the stretch, continued to battle on at the furlong marker but needed another gear late to hold off the closing winner in the end. SYSTEMATIC sat behind the frontrunner under a snug hold down the backside, waited inside throughout the turn, angled out bumping her rival at the eighth pole and needed more late to threaten for the win. OLD SECRETS travelled in the last flight with runners on either side at the half, was ridden between horses midway on the turn, found some late interest in mid stretch and passed tiring runners getting up late for a minor share. STERLING SPEED had a tracking position between foes in the second flight into the turn, bid three wide in upper stretch, was bumped by her inside rival at the furlong marker, lost action and lost a position late at the wire. VERY SAVVY stalked four deep in midfield at the half, was asked for more run three eighths from home, could not quicken with runners and weakened six wide at the top of the stretch. CLEOMENES was slow into stride at the break, trailed the field down the backside, stalked three wide outside runners at the rear three furlongs left to run and had nothing to offer between horses in the stretch drive. RIDERS CLAIM OF FOUL AND STEWARDS INQUIRY AT THE EIGHTH POLE REGARDING #1 SYSTEMATIC AND #5 STERLING SPEED RESULTED IN #1 SYSTEMATIC BEING DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED FIFTH FOR INTERFERENCE.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOUPER FLASHY tracked the early speed on the rail, was patiently handled inside throughout the turn, rallied between horses in the two path at the furlong marker, got clear late and was drawing away at the wire. MIMI'S GOLDEN RING broke a touch behind the field at the start, took command down the backside, repelled a brief outside challenge at the quarter pole, stubbornly fought on in deep stretch but could not hold off the closing winner at the finish. SWINGING MANDY was shuffled back to last running on the fence down the backside, was behind runners on the rail looking for a path as she turned for home, drifted in under right handed urging in upper stretch and straightened out late showing energy to get up for third at the finish line. SACRED DANCER settled down the backstretch in the middle of the pack in the three path, was under a hold between horses at the three eighths marker, shifted outside midway on the turn to start a rally, loomed five wide in upper stretch and ran evenly late losing third at the wire by a nod. AMERICAN GAMBLE tracked outside in the five path in the early going, began to take closer order three wide into the turn, battled outside for the lead two furlongs from the prize, was in with a chance as they turned for home but stalled in mid stretch. ANAM CARA broke with the field but quickly was relegated to trail at the half, offered a mild move four wide entering the turn and had nothing to give for the stretch drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MILLIE GIRL was on hold in last nearing the half on the rail, had a good inside position watching the three horses battle throughout the turn, angled out four wide at the top of the lane for run and wore down her rivals in the stretch edging clear in the final one hundred yards. LADY MOONSHINE broke in at the start, pressed for the lead on the rail into the turn, fought on gamely inside at the top of the stretch, could not match strides with the top two in mid stretch and settled for a clear third in the end. TEMPEREYA had a stalking position three wide at the half near the rear, ran four wide on the turn making no headway, angled in to the rail for the stretch drive and had little to show running late.
